  "title": "The Neolithic Transition in Britain",
  "abstract": "Abstract The explicit discussion of the beginning of the Neolithic in Britain has been in progress for little more than a century, in which time a bewildering range of interpretations have been proposed. This chapter attempts to recapitulate and evaluate some of the principal contributions, not simply as a kind of background to contemporary debates, but in order to reveal the derivation of arguments that may today be implicit or unacknowledged. It considers the views of Vere Gordon Childe, Stuart Piggott and Jacquetta Hawkes, Grahame Clark, Humphrey Case Alasdair Whittle, Robin Dennell, Ian Kinnes, Ian Hodder, Julian Thomas, Gabriel Cooney, Alison Sheridan, and Peter Rowley-Conwy.",
